==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Atlantic
<hw>At*lan"tic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Atlanticus</ets>, fr. <ets>Atlas</ets>. See <er>Atlas</er> and
<er>Atlantes</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to Mt. Atlas
in Libya, and hence applied to the ocean which lies between Europe and
Africa on the east and America on the west; <as>as, the
<ex>Atlantic</ex> Ocean (called also <ex>the Atlantic</ex>); the
<ex>Atlantic</ex> basin; the <ex>Atlantic</ex> telegraph.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the isle of Atlantis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Descended from Atlas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The seven <qex>Atlantic</qex> sisters.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atlantides</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
